        body: 'Industrial construction involves the design and building of facilities used for manufacturing, processing, storage, distribution and heavy industrial operations. Unlike residential or commercial construction, industrial facilities are designed around functional requirements such as production workflows, equipment installation, material handling and environmental controls. Common industrial construction projects in Tanzania include manufacturing plants for food processing, textiles, cement and consumer goods; warehouses and logistics centres for storage and distribution; agro-processing facilities for crops such as cashew nuts, coffee, tea and tobacco; and specialised facilities such as cold storage, chemical plants and mineral processing operations. Industrial construction requires specialised engineering knowledge, understanding of industrial processes and compliance with stringent safety and environmental regulations.'
