      { q: 'How long does hotel construction take?', a: 'Hotel construction timelines vary by size and complexity. A boutique hotel with 20-40 rooms typically takes 12 to 18 months. A mid-size resort with 50-100 rooms takes 18 to 30 months. Large hotels with over 150 rooms plus extensive facilities can take 24 to 48 months from design to completion.' },
      { q: 'What materials are used for hotel construction?', a: 'Hotel construction uses a combination of locally sourced materials such as stone and timber for architectural character, and specialised finishes for durability and aesthetics. Materials must be durable for high-traffic public areas, comfortable for guest rooms, and resistant to salt corrosion in coastal locations like Zanzibar.' },
      { q: 'How much does hotel construction cost in Tanzania?', a: 'Hotel construction costs in Tanzania vary widely by quality level and location. Budget and mid-range hotels range from TZS 1,500,000 to 3,000,000 per m2. Luxury hotels and resorts typically cost TZS 3,500,000 to 6,000,000 per m2 or more, depending on finishes, facilities and location. Zanzibar projects often command premium prices due to logistics.' },
      { q: 'What is special about hotel construction?', a: 'Hotel construction requires specialised attention to sound insulation between rooms, complex mechanical and electrical systems for guest comfort, stringent fire safety requirements, efficient back-of-house layouts for operations, and high-quality finishes that create memorable guest experiences. The design must balance aesthetics with operational efficiency.' },
      { q: 'Who builds hotels in Tanzania?', a: 'Hotels in Tanzania are built by registered contractors with experience in hospitality construction. International hotel brands often require contractors approved by their technical services team. Local contractors with hotel experience, such as those who have completed projects in Dar es Salaam, Arusha and Zanzibar, are well positioned for these projects.' }
