        body: 'Construction quality control is the systematic process of ensuring that construction work meets the specified standards, drawings, specifications and contractual requirements. It involves inspecting, testing and monitoring all aspects of construction from incoming materials to finished work, identifying defects or non-conformances and ensuring they are corrected. Quality control is an integral part of construction management that protects the owners investment, ensures structural safety and extends the lifespan of the building. In Tanzania, quality control has become increasingly important as building regulations are more strictly enforced and as property buyers and financiers demand evidence of quality compliance. Effective quality control requires a planned approach with clear standards, trained personnel, proper testing equipment and thorough documentation at every stage of construction.'
